  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowerment, Equality and Education in Rwanda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since the genocide in Rwanda there has been an increase in mental illness and loss of speech related to post traumatic stress. Despite this, schools in Rwanda don&#x2019;t really provide for disabled children. This project will ensure that disabled children can go to school despite the many challenges and lack of funding. It will train teachers and volunteer assistants so they can support these children properly. It will also provide speech therapy and specific help for children with difficulties hearing or talking, such as teaching them sign language. The project will work to change attitudes towards disabled people, and give these children the chance to contribute to society fully when they grow up. By the end of the project, it will have developed an example for Rwanda that will be promoted to the government and to other development organisations.</narrative>
  </description>
